  "dct_description_sm": [
    "World Latitude and Longitude Grid, 2022 is a line theme that represents a 1- by 1-degree latitude-longitude grid covering the world with attributes that allow it to display grids at intervals of 1, 5, 10, 15, 20, and 30 degrees. To display a grid with a 1-degree interval, display all of the lines. To display a coarser grid (for example, a 15-degree interval), in the Symbology pane in ArcGIS Pro or in the Layer Properties dialog box under the Symbology tab in ArcMap, choose the DEGREE15 field and value Y."
  ],
